'''October 5''' is the 5th day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=|12=draft}}  the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft}}  day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|qq=|12=draft}} . 
== Events ==

* {{ill|Eiso (Japan)|ja|永祚 (日本)|qq=|12=draft}}  2 ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|990|ja|990th year|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|October 26|ja|10月26日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Ichijō|ja|一条天皇|qq=|12=draft}} 's {{ill|Nyōgo|ja|女御|qq=|12=draft}} , {{ill|Fujiwara no Teishi|ja|藤原定子|qq=|12=draft}} , is elevated to the Rank of consort. Since the positions of {{ill|Grand Empress Dowager|ja|太皇太后|qq=|12=draft}} , {{ill|Empress Dowager|ja|皇太后|qq=|12=draft}} , and {{ill|Chūgū|ja|中宮|qq=|12=draft}}  were already filled by {{ill|Imperial Princess Masako|ja|昌子内親王|qq=|12=draft}} , {{ill|Fujiwara no Senshi|ja|藤原詮子|qq=|12=draft}} , and {{ill|Fujiwara no Junshi|ja|藤原遵子|qq=|12=draft}} , respectively, Junshi was designated as "Empress Palace" (皇后宮), while Teishi was called "Chūgū," marking the first instance of two consorts holding the Rank of empress simultaneously.

* {{ill|Kōgen (Japan)|ja|康元|qq=|12=draft}}  1 (Julian {{ill|1256|ja|1256th year|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|October 24|ja|10月24日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – The era name changes from {{ill|Kenchō (era)|ja|建長|qq=|12=draft}}  to Kōgen.

* {{ill|Bun'ei|ja|文永|qq=|12=draft}}  11 (Julian {{ill|1274|ja|1274th year|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 4|ja|11月4日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – The {{ill|Mongol Empire|ja|元 (王朝)|qq=|12=draft}}  invades Tsushima and Iki for the first time, beginning the {{ill|Battle of Bun'ei|ja|文永の役|qq=|12=draft}} .

* {{ill|Meitoku|ja|明徳|qq=|12=draft}}  3 / {{ill|Genchū|ja|元中|qq=|12=draft}}  9 (Intercalary October) (Julian {{ill|1392|ja|1392nd year|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 19|ja|11月19日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – The {{ill|Nanboku-chō period|ja|南北朝時代 (日本)|qq=|12=draft}}  ends as the {{ill|Southern Court (Japan)|ja|南朝 (日本)|qq=|12=draft}} 's {{ill|Go-Kameyama|ja|後亀山天皇|qq=|12=draft}}  surrenders the {{ill|Imperial Regalia of Japan|ja|三種の神器|1=Imperial Regalia of Japan|lt=Three Sacred Treasures|qq=|12=draft}}  to the {{ill|Northern Court (Japan)|ja|北朝 (日本)|qq=|12=draft}} 's {{ill|Go-Komatsu|ja|後小松天皇|qq=|12=draft}} , finalizing the {{ill|Meitoku Agreement|ja|明徳の和約|qq=|12=draft}} .

== Births ==

* {{ill|An'ei|ja|安永|qq=|12=draft}}  2 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1773|ja|1773rd year|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 18|ja|11月18日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Ienari|ja|徳川家斉|qq=|12=draft}} , 11th {{ill|Shōgun|ja|将軍|qq=|12=draft}}  of the {{ill|Edo shogunate|ja|Tokugawa shogunate|qq=|12=draft}}  (+ {{ill|1841|ja|1841st year|qq=|12=draft}} ).

== Deaths ==

* {{ill|Keichō|ja|Keichō|qq=|12=draft}}  19 (Gregorian {{ill|1614|ja|1614th year|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 6|ja|11月6日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Kyōnyo|ja|教如|qq=|12=draft}} , monk of the {{ill|Jōdo Shinshū|ja|Jōdo Shinshū|qq=|12=draft}} , 12th {{ill|Hōshu|ja|法主|qq=|12=draft}}  of {{ill|Higashi Hongan-ji|ja|東本願寺|qq=|12=draft}}  (* {{ill|1558|ja|1558th year|qq=|12=draft}} ).

* {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|qq=|12=draft}}  7 (Gregorian {{ill|1630|ja|1630th year|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 9|ja|11月9日|qq=|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tōdō Takatora|ja|藤堂高虎|qq=|12=draft}} , {{ill|Samurai|ja|武将|qq=|12=draft}}  (* {{ill|1556|ja|1556th year|qq=|12=draft}} ).

